Hey welcome! This is my blog about cpu and software performance, main courses will be
SWAR tricks, bit-twiddling a bunch of simd, stopping the cpu from predicting the future
and whatever stupid low level stuff i find fun enough to write about.

I'm Giuseppe and currently the only person here. I put a genuinely stupid amount of effort 
into those posts and in the featured software!

If you're into this kind of stuff too and want to write something, hit me up, I'd love 
collabs. Genuinely. Co-authoring, guest posts, "Hey I think your benchmark is wrong",
everything welcome

Also: don't take anything here too seriously. I will absolutely get things wrong sometimes,
I will absolutely make jokes about it, and if you spot a mistake, telling me is a gift,
not an attack. This is a silly billy blog written by someone who cares too much.

## A small ask

If you used something from here and it made your code faster, I'd love to hear about it.  

If you published something where this blog helped you get there, let me know too — it would 
genuinely make my day.

## Contacts

- **[giuseppecesarano@extractingcycles.com](mailto:giuseppecesarano@extractingcycles.com)** — for collabs, corrections, "your benchmark is wrong" emails, whatever.
- **[My GitHub](https://github.com/GiuseppeCesarano)** — where the rest of my questionable code lives.
- **[extractingcycles.com source](https://github.com/GiuseppeCesarano/extractingcycles)** — yes, the blog itself is open source, go poke around. Or open an issue if you find a better way to do something.

